Package fr.lirmm.chocominer.app.specialized.algorithm.runners

Interface AlgorithmRunnerInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractIMAlgorithmRunner, AbstractPRIRunner, AprioriCloseRunner, AprioriInverseRunner, AprioriInverseTIDRunner, AprioriRareRunner, AprioriRunner, CharmBitSetRunner, CharmMFIRunner, CORIRunner, DCharmBitSetRunner, DEclatBitSetRunner, DEclatRunner, DefMeRunner, FPCloseRunner, FPGrowthRunner, FPMaxRunner, LCMFreqRunner, LCMRunner, ZartFrequentRunner, ZartRunner
public interface AlgorithmRunnerInterface
An algorithm runner defines a strategy for how a certain SPMF algorithm should be executed. SPMF algorithms often have varying methods and parameters, they may even depend on other algorithms to function. Runners take care of this problem. This decouples the responsibility of Solving Strategies wherein they do not have to worry how to run a certain algorithm.
Author:
Theodore Picot
